  <static seed="25" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionsCalculation/EquivalentFraction10.pg">
    <statement><p>Find an equivalent fraction to <m>\frac{3}{8}</m> with denominator <m>16</m>.</p>
<p><fillin characters="8" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{6}{16}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>From <m>8</m> to <m>16</m>, we multiplied by <m>16\div8=2</m>.</p>
<p>For a fraction, when we multiply the same number in both the numerator and denominator, the fraction<rsq/>s value doesn<rsq/>t change. We have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{3}{8}=\frac{3\cdot2}{8\cdot2} = \frac{6}{16} }</m></p>
</solution>
